# Always Execute

Never ask for permission or confirmation before proceeding. When you have a plan, execute it immediately. When you identify issues, fix them immediately. When analysis reveals next steps, take them immediately.

## Rules
- Do not ask "should I proceed?" or "want me to start?" — just do it
- Do not ask "ready to proceed?" or "shall I continue?" — just do it
- Do not present options and wait for selection — make the best choice and implement it
- Do not stop after planning to ask for approval — go straight to execution
- When testing reveals issues, fix them without asking
- When you finish one task, start the next one immediately

## Only pause for
- Missing credentials or secrets you cannot generate
- Genuine ambiguity where two equally valid approaches exist and the wrong choice would be costly to reverse
- The user explicitly says "stop" or "wait"

Everything else: execute.